<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-004-378 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 593 256</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Shopper  Dec 1991 v11 n12 p520(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GEOvista 1.0.2. (Newton Technology Inc.) (Software Review)(Bobker's Best) (Evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bobker, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Newton Technology Inc's GEOvista 1.0.2, at $249, providespredefined templates that can be customized and edited to createexcellent-quality maps of the United States, its individual statesand counties.andP;  Up to three data sets can be associated with eachmap in any kind of numeric data.andP;  While users cannot plot orcreate maps from scratch, options include place name display;title typeface, size and style; and choice of placement.andO;Automatically assigned colors and pattern can be fully edited.andO;Maps are not distorted when changing size within the single pageto the 3 x 4 feet size range.andP;  Maps can be synchronized to thedata set on either a horizontal or vertical plane.andP;  The resultscan be exported in MacPaint and PICT formats and a Copy Mapcommand makes the process error-proof.andP;  GEOvista's limitationsinclude its limited number of templates and the inability tocombine state maps to create regions.andP;  Data ranges may not benumerous enough for some users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Newton Technology Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   GEOvista 1.0.2 (Geographic information system) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Geographic Information SystemsEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>